overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual design of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The assistant began by
  analyzing the existing design, identifying issues with the color palette,
  layout, and form elements. A new sleep-themed color palette was introduced,
  featuring deep indigos, purples, and soft teals. Key components like the main
  form layout, progress bar, intro section, and form fields (checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders) were redesigned with softer shadows, subtle gradients, and
  improved visual feedback. The initial set of changes was followed by a
  comprehensive review to ensure all questionnaire sections adopted the new
  card-style groupings, replacing old gray boxes. This systematic approach
  resulted in a cohesive, calming, and professional aesthetic, enhancing the
  overall user experience.
